    <string name="about_content_about">"
<![CDATA[
<h1> AndroFotoFinder </h1>
</p>
Features:
<ul>
  <li>Can handle big image collections (15000+ images in 1000+ folders)</li>
  <li>Uses Android's image content-provider. No initial image scan neccessary.</li>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/k3b/AndroFotoFinder/wiki/Filter-View">Find images</a> via</li>
  <ul>
    <li>folder (with hirachical <a href="https://github.com/k3b/AndroFotoFinder/wiki/Folder-Picker">Folder-Picker</a>)&nbsp;</li>
    <li>wildcards that match folder/filename&nbsp;</li>
    <li>date&nbsp;</li>
    <li>area in <a href="https://github.com/k3b/AndroFotoFinder/wiki/geographic-map">geographic map</a> (if image has gps-exif info)
    </li>
  </ul>
  <li>Show result in a scrollable <a href="https://github.com/k3b/AndroFotoFinder/wiki/Gallery-View">gallery view</a> with</li>
  <ul>
    <li>support for multible photo selection (since 0.4.0)</li>
    <li>file operations copy, move, delete, share (since 0.4.0)</li>
  </ul>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/k3b/AndroFotoFinder/wiki/Image-View">Photo-detail-view</a> with</li>
  <li><ul>
    <li>image zoom</li>
    <li>swipe to go to next/previous image</li>
    <li>show extended image info (Exif, IPTC, XMP, ICC)</li>
    <li>file operations copy, move, delete, rename, share (since 0.4.1)</li>
  </ul></li>
  <li>The <a href="https://github.com/k3b/AndroFotoFinder/wiki/geographic-map">geografic map</a> shows markers at places where photos were
 taken</li>
  <li>File operations</li>
  <li><ul>
    <li>will also update Android's image content-provider-database</li>
    <li>update xmp-sidecar-files</li>
    <li>preserve file date if local android supports it.</li>
  </ul></li>
</ul>
<br />
]]>
